                    "status": "open",
                    "priority": "medium",
                    "reviewer": "reviewer-teaching-assistant",
                    "content": {
                      "runs": [
                        {"type": "text", "text": "I agree with the major revision request. Here's a suggested expansion:"}
                      ]
                    },
                    "suggestedChange": {
                      "runs": [
                        {"type": "text", "text": "There are three main types of machine learning:\n\n• **Supervised Learning**: The algorithm learns from labeled training data to make predictions on new data. For example, training a model to recognize handwritten digits using thousands of labeled digit images.\n\n• **Unsupervised Learning**: The algorithm finds patterns in data without labeled examples. For instance, clustering customers based on purchasing behavior without knowing predefined customer types.\n\n• **Reinforcement Learning**: The algorithm learns through trial and error by receiving rewards or penalties for actions. A classic example is training a computer to play chess by playing many games and learning from wins and losses."}
                      ]
                    },
